Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the Fr\'echet distance, which is a well-studied measure of similarity of two curves in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithmic approach to compute the Fr\'echet distance on c-packed curves, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves studying the properties of c-packed curves, which are a restricted class of curves, and analyzing the complexity of computing the Fr\'echet distance on them. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The Fr\'echet distance has applications in analyzing and comparing trajectories in social and information networks, making this sub-category a possible fit. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the lower bounds on the complexity of computing the Fr\'echet distance on c-packed curves, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
